`CommandExecutor` interface to handle various commands related to cities in a Minecraft plugin.\\n\\n`CityCommand`: This class handles various city-related commands such as creating a city, setting the city spawn, teleporting to a city, removing a city, leaving a city, liking a city, viewing city information, accepting/denying city invites, inviting players, promoting/demoting players, claiming/unclaiming chunks, depositing/withdrawing from the city bank, and listing all cities.\\n\\n`onCommand`: This function is the main entry point for the `CityCommand` class, which processes the various city-related commands based on the arguments provided.\\n\\n`isLeader`: This function checks if the player is the leader of the city they belong to.\\n\\n`isLeaderOrCoLeader`: This function checks if the player is the leader or co-leader of the city they belong to.\\n\\n`formatLoc`: This function formats a location object into a string representation.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/manager/CityEconomyManager.java\":\"This file contains a single class, `CityEconomyManager`, which provides methods for managing the economy of a city, including getting the balance, setting the balance, depositing, withdrawing, and checking if a user has enough funds.\\n\\n`CityEconomyManager`: A class that manages the economy of a city, including handling balance operations and transactions.\\n\\n`getBalance(UUID uuid)`: Retrieves the current balance of the specified user.\\n`setBalance(UUID uuid, double amount)`: Sets the balance of the specified user to the given amount.\\n`deposit(UUID uuid, double amount)`: Deposits the specified amount into the user\\u0027s account.\\n`withdraw(UUID uuid, double amount)`: Withdraws the specified amount from the user\\u0027s account, if they have enough funds.\\n`hasEnough(UUID uuid, double amount)`: Checks if the specified user has enough funds to withdraw the given amount.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/ui/CityGUIListener.java\":\"This file contains a single class `CityGUIListener` that implements the `Listener` interface. The class listens for `InventoryClickEvent` events and handles the user interactions with the city management GUI.\\n\\n`CityGUIListener`: Handles user interactions with the city management GUI.\\n\\n`onInventoryClick(InventoryClickEvent event)`: Listens for inventory click events and performs actions based on the clicked item and the current GUI menu.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/listener/CityInviteListener.java\":\"This file contains a single class `CityInviteListener` that implements the `Listener` interface and handles various events related to city management in a Minecraft server plugin.\\n\\n`CityInviteListener`: This class listens for player chat events and handles city-related actions such as inviting players, promoting players to co-leader, and demoting players within a city.\\n\\n`onChat`: This function is called when a player sends a chat message. It checks if the player is awaiting input for a city-related action (invite, promote, or demote) and processes the input accordingly.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/manager/CityManager.java\":\"This file contains a single class, `CityManager`, which is responsible for managing the cities in a Minecraft server. Here\\u0027s a summary of the class and its functions:\\n\\n`CityManager`: Manages the cities in a Minecraft server, including creating, updating, and removing cities, as well as managing city members and their ranks.\\n\\n`getCityName(UUID uuid)`: Returns the name of the city that the given player is a member of, or `null` if the player is not a member of any city.\\n\\n`getCityId(UUID uuid)`: Returns the ID of the city that the given player is a member of, or `-1` if the player is not a member of any city.\\n\\n`getCityNameById(int cityId)`: Returns the name of the city with the given ID, or \\\"Inconnue\\\" if the city is not found.\\n\\n`getCityRank(UUID uuid)`: Returns the rank of the given player in their city, or `null` if the player is not a member of any city.\\n\\n`setMember(String cityName, UUID uuid, CityRank rank)`: Sets the rank of the given player in the given city.\\n\\n`removeMember(UUID uuid)`: Removes the given player from their city.\\n\\n`createCity(UUID owner, String name, Location loc)`: Creates a new city with the given owner, name, and location.\\n\\n`updateCitySpawn(String cityName, Location loc)`: Updates the spawn location of the given city.\\n\\n`getCityLocation(String cityName)`: Returns the spawn location of the given city, or `null` if the city is not found.\\n\\n`hasCity(UUID uuid)`: Returns `true` if the given player is a member of a city, `false` otherwise.\\n\\n`removeCity(UUID uuid)`: Removes the city that the given player is a member of.\\n\\n`hasLikedCity(UUID uuid, String cityName)`: Returns `true` if the given player has liked the given city, `false` otherwise.\\n\\n`likeCity(UUID uuid, String cityName)`: Adds a like to the given city by the given player.\\n\\n`getLikes(UUID uuid)`: Returns the number of likes for the city that the given player is a member of, or 0 if the player is not a member of any city.\\n\\n`getSortedMembersByRank(String cityName)`: Returns a list of the UUIDs of the members of the given city, sorted by their rank.\\n\\n`parseMembers(String json)`: Parses a JSON string representing a map of player UUIDs to their ranks in a city.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/CityRank.java\":\"This file defines an enumeration `CityRank` that represents the different ranks within a city, such as \\\"Leader\\\", \\\"Co-leader\\\", and \\\"Member\\\". Each rank has a corresponding display name that can be retrieved using the `getDisplayName()` method. The `fromString()` method allows converting a string value to the corresponding `CityRank` instance.\\n\\n`CityRank`: An enumeration that represents the different ranks within a city.\\n\\n`getDisplayName()`: Returns the display name of the `CityRank` instance.\\n\\n`fromString()`: Converts a string value to the corresponding `CityRank` instance.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/manager/ClaimManager.java\":\"This file contains a single class, `ClaimManager`, which is responsible for managing the claims of cities in a Minecraft server.\\n\\n`ClaimManager`: A class that manages the claims of cities in a Minecraft server, including claiming and unclaiming chunks, checking if a chunk is claimed, and getting the owner of a chunk.\\n\\n`claimChunk(int cityId, Chunk chunk)`: Adds a new claim for the specified city on the given chunk.\\n`unclaimChunk(int cityId, Chunk chunk)`: Removes the claim for the specified city on the given chunk.\\n`isChunkClaimed(Chunk chunk)`: Checks if the given chunk is claimed by any city.\\n`getChunkOwnerId(Location loc)`: Retrieves the ID of the city that owns the chunk at the given location.\\n`getClaimCount(int cityId)`: Retrieves the number of chunks claimed by the specified city.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/listener/ChunkProtectionListener.java\":\"This file contains a single class, `ChunkProtectionListener`, which implements the `Listener` interface. The class is responsible for handling block break and player interaction events, and ensuring that players can only interact with blocks within the boundaries of a claimed city.\\n\\n`ChunkProtectionListener`: A class that listens for block break and player interaction events, and cancels the events if the player is not authorized to interact with the block based on the city claim.\\n\\n`onBreak(BlockBreakEvent)`: A method that listens for block break events and cancels the event if the player is not authorized to break the block based on the city claim.\\n\\n`onInteract(PlayerInteractEvent)`: A method that listens for player interaction events and cancels the event if the player is not authorized to interact with the block based on the city claim.\\n\\n`checkAccess(UUID, Location)`: A method that checks whether a player is authorized to interact with a block based on the city claim at the given location.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/ui/CityGUI.java\":\"This file contains a single class `CityGUI` which is responsible for managing the graphical user interface (GUI) for a city-based plugin in a Minecraft server.\\n\\n`CityGUI`: Manages the GUI for displaying a list of cities, their information, and providing options for players to interact with the city system.\\n\\n`openCityList`: Opens the GUI for displaying the list of cities sorted by the number of likes.\\n`createCustomPaperItem`: Creates a custom paper item with a specified name and lore.\\n`getCityBanner`: Retrieves the banner item for a given city name from the database.\\n`deserializeBanner`: Deserializes a banner item from a base64-encoded string.\\n`getCitiesSortedByLikes`: Retrieves a list of city entries sorted by the number of likes.\\n`translateHex`: Translates a hexadecimal color code into a Minecraft color code.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/listener/CityEnterListener.java\":\"This file contains a single class, `CityEnterListener`, which implements the `Listener` interface. The class is responsible for handling player movement events and updating the player\\u0027s current territory based on their location.\\n\\n`CityEnterListener`: A class that listens for player movement events and updates the player\\u0027s current territory based on their location.\\n\\n`onMove`: Handles the `PlayerMoveEvent` and calls the `handleTerritoryChange` method.\\n`onTeleport`: Handles the `PlayerTeleportEvent` and calls the `handleTerritoryChange` method.\\n`onJoin`: Handles the `PlayerJoinEvent` and calls the `handleTerritoryChange` method.\\n`handleTerritoryChange`: Determines the player\\u0027s current territory based on their location and updates the player\\u0027s title accordingly.\\n`isInSpawnRegion`: Checks if the player is currently in the \\\"spawn\\\" region.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/commands/CityAdminCommand.java\":\"`CityAdminCommand`: This class implements the `CommandExecutor` interface to handle the `/city admin` command in the Bukkit plugin.\\n\\n`onCommand`: This function is called when the `/city admin` command is executed. It checks if the sender is an operator or the console, and if so, it applies a 7% interest to the bank balance of all cities in the database.\\n\\nThis file contains a Bukkit plugin command that allows server administrators to apply a 7% interest to the bank balance of all cities in the database.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/listener/CityChatListener.java\":\"This file contains a single class `CityChatListener` that implements the `Listener` interface and listens for `AsyncPlayerChatEvent` events. The class handles various city-related actions, such as creating a new city, depositing or withdrawing funds from a city\\u0027s bank, and updating a city\\u0027s spawn point.\\n\\n`CityChatListener`: Listens for player chat events and handles various city-related actions.\\n\\n`onChat`: Handles player chat events and performs different actions based on the message content, such as creating a new city, depositing or withdrawing funds, or updating a city\\u0027s spawn point.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/manager/CityBankManager.java\":\"This file contains a single class, `CityBankManager`, which provides methods for managing the bank balances of cities.\\n\\n`CityBankManager`: A class that manages the bank balances of cities, including retrieving the balance, depositing and withdrawing funds, and applying interest to all city bank balances.\\n\\n`getBalance(int cityId)`: Retrieves the current bank balance of the city with the specified ID.\\n\\n`deposit(int cityId, double amount)`: Deposits the specified amount of money into the bank account of the city with the specified ID.\\n\\n`withdraw(int cityId, double amount)`: Withdraws the specified amount of money from the bank account of the city with the specified ID, if the balance is sufficient.\\n\\n`applyInterest(double percentage)`: Applies the specified percentage of interest to the bank balances of all cities.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/ui/CityManageGUI.java\":\"This file contains a single class `CityManageGUI` that provides a graphical user interface (GUI) for managing a city in a Minecraft server.\\n\\n`CityManageGUI`: Provides a GUI for managing a city, including options to protect zones, set the spawn point, modify the city\\u0027s banner, and view and manage city members.\\n\\n`open(Player player)`: Opens the city management GUI for the specified player, displaying the available options and city information.\\n\\n`createItem(String name, String... lore)`: Creates a new `ItemStack` with the specified name and lore, used to populate the GUI.\\n\\n`createPlayerHead(OfflinePlayer player, String displayName)`: Creates a new `ItemStack` representing a player\\u0027s head, with the specified display name, used to display city members in the GUI.\",\"/src/main/java/fr/rudy/cities/CitiesPlugin.java\":\"This file is the main class of the CitiesPlugin, which is a Bukkit plugin for a Minecraft server. It handles the initialization and management of the plugin, including the database connection, various managers, commands, and event listeners.\\n\\n`CitiesPlugin`: The main class of the plugin, responsible for initializing the plugin, managing the database connection, and providing access to various managers.\\n\\n`get()`: A static method that returns the instance of the `CitiesPlugin` class.\\n\\n`getPendingInvites()`: Returns a map of pending city invites.\\n\\n`onEnable()`: The method called when the plugin is enabled, which sets up the database connection, creates necessary tables, initializes managers, registers commands and event listeners.\\n\\n`onDisable()`: The method called when the plugin is disabled, which closes the database connection.\\n\\n`getCityManager()`: Returns the `CityManager` instance.\\n\\n`getCityBankManager()`: Returns the `CityBankManager` instance.\\n\\n`getClaimManager()`: Returns the `ClaimManager` instance.\\n\\n`getDatabase()`: Returns the database connection.\\n\\n`getCityEconomy()`: Returns the `CityEconomyManager` instance.\"}"}
